Description: Four fragments of open, plain weave, wool textile wrapping. The fabric colour probably was originally red and the yarn is fine. The spinning direction of the warp and weft is 's' and the warp thread count is 8, while the weft thread count is 11. Fragments of binding (93.1.248D) still adhere.
Bibliographic references: Adams et al 1999 / Kulubnarti III: The Cemeteries (p.65)
Condition: Two of the fragments are in tight wads.
Acquisition name: Donated by: Dr William Yewdale Adams
Donated by: W S Webb Museum of Anthropology (University of Kentucky)
Additional IDs: Excavation/small finds number: 93.1.248C (excavation object cat. no.)
